  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      TO ANALYSE THE EFFICACY AND SAFETY OF ENDOSCOPIC BAND LIGATION WITHOUT RESECTION IN SMALL
      GASTROINTESTINAL SUBMUCOSAL TUMORS
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Multicenter Prospective study analysing the efficacy and safety of endoscopic band ligation
      without resection in small (&lt;15mm) gastrointestinal submucosal tumor.

      This endoscopic technique will be complemented with SINK (single incissional needle-knife)
      for ensuring the AP diagnosis of the trated submucosa tumour
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
