  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        PATIENTS WITH SUBMUCOSAL TUMORS IN THE GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age between 18 and 80 years.

          -  Endoscopic ultrasound image of subepithelial tumour gastrointestinal TSM &lt; or equal to
             15mm.

          -  Patient able to sign and understand the informed consent.

          -  Patient that understand the concept of the study and will complete all the time frame
             until the study end.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy or lactancy

          -  Severe coagulation disorders: INR&gt; 1.5 not correctable with administration of plasma
             and / or platelets &lt;50,000 / mm3.

          -  Vascular subepithelial lesions (Doppler imaging Endoscopic Ultrasound).

          -  Subepithelial tumors with clear diagnostic of EUS benign semiology: lipoma; Ectopic
             pancreas.

          -  Subepithelial tumors&gt; 15mm.

          -  No informed consent.

          -  In case of patients with mental retardation, without the ability to understand the
             nature and possible consequences of the study, except the existence of a legal
             representative.

          -  Patients unable to maintain subsequent follow-up (lack of adherence).

          -  Situations that do not allow the practice of a digestive endoscopy (eg, stenosis).

          -  Patients with a prognosis of life less than 12 months.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
